# Immutable Entity Pattern

- Backend domain entities are immutable.
- Prefer readonly public fields.
- Use a private constructor when it fits the existing entity style.
- Call `Object.freeze(this)` at the end of the constructor.
- State-changing methods must return a new entity instance instead of mutating the current one.
- Static factories such as `create(...)` and `hydrate(...)` are acceptable and already used in this repository.
- Persistence snapshot methods should stay pure and should not mutate entity state.
